                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="247979" author="bevans" created="Wed, 29 May 2019 17:09:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10698&quot; title=&quot;Specify complex JobIDs for Lustre&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-10698&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-10698&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="226446" author="adilger" created="Fri, 20 Apr 2018 03:29:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;For reproducer, just enable jobstats on the client (e.g. &lt;tt&gt;lctl set_param jobid_var=procname_uid&lt;/tt&gt;), run &quot;&lt;tt&gt;ls -l&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; on a directory, and check jobstats on the server(s). &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="226436" author="bevans" created="Thu, 19 Apr 2018 23:27:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll take a look, is there a good reproducer I can use to see the problem?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="226430" author="adilger" created="Thu, 19 Apr 2018 22:00:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is still an issue with 2.10.1 at least.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ben, is there any chance you could look into this?  I think passing on the &quot;parent&quot; JobID from the process running &quot;ls&quot; to the statahead thread would be best.  It &lt;em&gt;might&lt;/em&gt; be possible to pass environment variables to new threads via &lt;tt&gt;kthread_create()&lt;/tt&gt; at launch time, but I&apos;m not positive.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
